File: platform/mcp-server/src/browser-tools/analyze-site/detect-apis.ts, line 450.

The bug: At line 450, `frame.url !== ep.url` uses a strict equality comparison. But `ep.url` was normalized at lines 417-420 to `${parsed.origin}${parsed.pathname}` (no query string), while `frame.url` retains the raw URL which may include query parameters (e.g., `wss://example.com/ws?token=abc`). This means frames never match WebSocket endpoints that use query params.

Fix: Normalize `frame.url` the same way before comparison. At line 450, instead of `if (frame.url !== ep.url) continue;`, normalize frame.url:
```
let normalizedFrameUrl: string;
try {
  const parsed = new URL(frame.url);
  normalizedFrameUrl = `${parsed.origin}${parsed.pathname}`;
} catch {
  normalizedFrameUrl = frame.url;
}
if (normalizedFrameUrl !== ep.url) continue;
```

Check platform/mcp-server/src/browser-tools/analyze-site/detect-apis.test.ts for existing tests. Add a test with wsFrames that have query params in their URLs.
